    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Q.4'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q4. What insight can be gained by comparing Sales and Profit together? Then explain how you would create a chart to analyze Profit by Sub-Category. Hint: Use Sub-Category as a Dimension and Profit as a Measure.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' underline='true'>Answer:-</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Insight from comparing Sales and Profit:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Comparing </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Sales and Profit</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> helps understand whether high sales are actually generating profit or not. It is possible that a product or category has high sales but low profit or even loss due to high discounts or costs. This comparison helps identify:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Profitable and unprofitable categories </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Impact of discounts on profit </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Overall business performance </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Chart to analyze Profit by Sub-Category:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>To analyze profit by sub-category in Tableau:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open a new worksheet </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Sub-Category</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> to the </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Columns</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> shelf </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Drag </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Profit</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> to the </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Rows</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> shelf </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau will automatically create a bar chart </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Ensure aggregation is </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>SUM(Profit)</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> (default)</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
