    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Q.5'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q5.  Create a Line Chart to show Sales Trend over Order Date. Which date level would you choose (Year / Quarter / Month)? Why are line charts suitable for time-based analysis? Hint: Drag Order Date and change its date hierarchy from Year to Month if needed.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' underline='true'>Answer:-</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Which date level would you choose?</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Month</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> is the most suitable date level.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Why are line charts suitable for time-based analysis?</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Line charts show </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>trends over time</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> clearly </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>They help visualize </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>increase or decrease patterns</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Useful for identifying </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>seasonality, growth, and fluctuations</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Easy to interpret continuous data over time </run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
