              <zone h='98000' id='5' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q8. What is the difference between a Worksheet and a Dashboard in Tableau? Why is a dashboard more useful for decision-makers?</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' underline='true'>Answer:-</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' fontsize='10'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='9' italic='false' underline='false'>Feature&#9;Worksheet&#9;Dashboard&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='false' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='9' italic='false' underline='false'>Purpose	        Create a single visualization	      Combine multiple visualizations
Content	        One chart/graph at a time           	Multiple charts, filters, and objects
Usage	        Basic data analysis	   Comprehensive data presentation
Interactio	        Limited	    Interactive (filters, actions, etc.)
</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='9' italic='false' underline='false'>Feature&#9;Worksheet&#9;Dashboard&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='false' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='9' italic='false' underline='false'>Purpose	        Create a single visualization	      Combine multiple visualizations
Content	        One chart/graph at a time           	Multiple charts, filters, and objects
Usage	        Basic data analysis	   Comprehensive data presentation
Interactio	        Limited	    Interactive (filters, actions, etc.)
</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{D883EE36-406F-40F4-B5C2-AB66BF133C18}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Q.9'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q9.  What is Tableau Prep, and why is it important in real-world data projects? What is Tableau Prep, and why is it important in real-world data projects? Then explain how you would: Remove null values Remove duplicate records Change incorrect data types (Answer in steps, no tool access required.)</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' underline='true'>Answer:-</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>What is Tableau Prep?</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau Prep</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> is a data preparation tool used to clean, combine, and organize raw data before analysis in Tableau. It helps transform messy data into a structured format suitable for visualization.</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Why is it important in real-world projects?</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Ensures </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>accurate and reliable data</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Helps in </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>cleaning and organizing large datasets</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Improves </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>data quality for better analysis</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Saves time by automating data preparation tasks </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Reduces errors in reporting and decision-making </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Data Cleaning Steps:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>1. Remove Null Values:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open the dataset in Tableau Prep </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify fields containing null values </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Use the filter option to exclude </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Null</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> values </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Apply the filter to remove unwanted records </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>2. Remove Duplicate Records:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Check for duplicate rows in the dataset </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Use the </run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Remove Duplicates</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> option or apply aggregation </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Keep only unique values based on required fields </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>3. Change Incorrect Data Types:</run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify fields with wrong data types (e.g., text instead of number) </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Click on the data type icon of the field </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Change it to the correct type (Number, Date, String, etc.) </run>
              <run>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Verify that data is correctly formatted</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='6' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='98000' id='5' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                <zone h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Q9.  What is Tableau Prep, and why is it important in real-world data projects? What is Tableau Prep, and why is it important in real-world data projects? Then explain how you would: Remove null values Remove duplicate records Change incorrect data types (Answer in steps, no tool access required.)</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book' underline='true'>Answer:-</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>What is Tableau Prep?</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Tableau Prep</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> is a data preparation tool used to clean, combine, and organize raw data before analysis in Tableau. It helps transform messy data into a structured format suitable for visualization.</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Why is it important in real-world projects?</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Ensures </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>accurate and reliable data</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Helps in </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>cleaning and organizing large datasets</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Improves </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>data quality for better analysis</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Æ </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Saves time by automating data preparation tasks </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Reduces errors in reporting and decision-making </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Data Cleaning Steps:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>1. Remove Null Values:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Open the dataset in Tableau Prep </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify fields containing null values </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Use the filter option to exclude </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Null</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> values </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Apply the filter to remove unwanted records </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>2. Remove Duplicate Records:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Check for duplicate rows in the dataset </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Use the </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Remove Duplicates</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'> option or apply aggregation </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Keep only unique values based on required fields </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>3. Change Incorrect Data Types:</run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Identify fields with wrong data types (e.g., text instead of number) </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Click on the data type icon of the field </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Change it to the correct type (Number, Date, String, etc.) </run>
                    <run>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Benton Sans Book'>Verify that data is correctly formatted</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
